snippet: The WikiLeaks founder has taken refuge in the Ecuadorean Embassy in London for two years while facing extradition to Sweden.
abstract: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange says that he will soon be leaving the Ecuadorean Embassy in London, where he was given asylum two years ago, but provides no specifics.
lead_paragraph: The WikiLeaks founder has taken refuge in the Ecuadorean Embassy in London for two years while facing extradition to Sweden.

headline.main: Julian Assange Says He Will Leave Embassy ‘Soon’
headline.print_headline: Assange Says He’ll Leave Embassy in London
